Peekadee
________________________________________________________________________________

A replacement for PQDI.

[000] Index
________________________________________________________________________________

* Dependencies ........................................................... [001]
* Building ............................................................... [002]
* Running  ............................................................... [003]
* Testing ................................................................ [004]
* Contributing ........................................................... [005]
* License ................................................................ [006]

[001] Dependencies
________________________________________________________________________________

* Go       [https://go.dev/learn/]
* Make     [https://www.gnu.org/software/make/]
* Docker   [https://docs.docker.com/engine/install/]

Additionally, to run the server(s), your environment must have all mandatory
environment variables present at runtime. See the `example.env` file.

[002] Building
________________________________________________________________________________

Building the service requires you to first generate the types declared in the
protocol definition, but assuming your environment is configured correctly the
build process is very simple:

+------------------------------------------------------------------------------+
|                                                                              |
|   $ git clone --recurse-submodules git@github.com:gebhn/peekadee.git         |
|   $ cd peekadee                                                              |
|                                                                              |
|   $ make develop   # Run docker containers                                   |
|   $ make generate  # Generate schema/sqlc codegen                            |
|   $ make           # Build                                                   |
|                                                                              |
+------------------------------------------------------------------------------+

[003] Running
________________________________________________________________________________

The server assumes access to a running instance of Redis and MySQL. You may wish 
to run these locally via Docker:

+------------------------------------------------------------------------------+
|                                                                              |
|   $ make develop                                                             |
|                                                                              |
+------------------------------------------------------------------------------+

See the associated documentation for more information regarding Redis and MySQL
respectively.

[004] Testing
________________________________________________________________________________

Testing is similarly simple and also requires a valid .env file:

+------------------------------------------------------------------------------+
|                                                                              |
|   $ make test         # To run unit tests                                    |
|   $ make count=n test # To run unit tests n times                            |
|                                                                              |
+------------------------------------------------------------------------------+

[005] Contributing
________________________________________________________________________________

Pull requests should be opened for review with individual commits and follow the
conventional commits guidelines.

